13/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police arrested 40 people on Tuesday (April 12th) for suspected links to al-Qaeda and the Turkish Hezbollah terror groups. The arrests were made in several synchronised raids across the country. Media reported that Halis Bayancuk, who has previously been described as the head of al-Qaeda in Turkey, was detained. (Zaman, Anadolu news agency - 12/04/11)
